ReferenceDocuments.name: Determination of fetal growth
ReferenceDocuments.description: Determination of fetal growth is a three-step process:  Step 1: Ascertainment of estimated fetal weight (EFW)  Step 2: Verification of gestational age (GA) at which the EFW was recorded  Step 3: Determination of EFW or biometry percentiles by plotting the EFW or relevant biometric measures at the appropriate GA on a pre-defined fetal growth curve
